				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MPG Trials<a name="67909"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 23 04 6:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yesterday I also did this trial, but we succeeded.  The key was massive DPS.  You don't get a message when you've killed the 20th mob *(within 15 min).  However, if it doesn't boot you out, you can then go engage the named.
<br />

<br />
Tips:
<br />

<br />
Don't worry about slow/mez/single pulling.  Use AE slow/dot and offtank stuff.  The mobs are about same DPS as norm LDON mobs, or less.
<br />

<br />
The reward for winning was a Quarm-quality shoulder, a glowing rune, and +8 to the maximum resists of everyone in the party. 
<br />

<br />
We also tried the one where you get bane weapons and stuff to kill the named, but failed that.  We decided a mage/bard combo for about 600 point DS is the key to winning that.  Also, a second healer would help.  I think the name was ingenuity, or something.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
