				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MPG Trials<a name="69348"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 9 04 3:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Anulien I recommend you wait the 2 hour lockout then win another trial.  Then check your timers....you may be surprised.
<br />

<br />
The trials are very fun and a fast way to get loot and glowing runes.  In my experience, runes drop about 1 in 2.  It is streaky though, I went a day with 4 trial wins, and not one rune.
<br />

<br />
I have some pretty decent loot from these trials, and the best part is that the slots are ones that are commonly harder to upgrade (shoulders, belt, ring, ear, face, etc.).  It takes about 20 minutes to clear to a projection from hub, which you can basically invis to.  From the Projection, each trial is about 25ish minutes, assuming no one has any timers still active.  So a good balanced group can do it start to finish in an hour.  
<br />

<br />
Bards are very key to just about every trial, so you shouldn't have issues with invites, like some classes do.
<br />

<br />
A few quick tips on some of the trials:
<br />

<br />
Subversion - All roamers are lullable with SSoQ.  Easy trial to do if you bring a rogue to do chests while you lull.  Alternately, have a cleric lull and you do the mechanical traps.
<br />

<br />
Destruction - I don't bother mezzing slowing in these, just jack up the DS and go to town.  If you get behind on killing you will likely fail, as the mobs can pile up.  The named in this trial is a joke.  He was dead before Kinsong wore off.
<br />

<br />
Fear - Bard fear does not work on any of the light blue fearable mobs.  Bard's job is to mez the dark blues, and slow mobs.  Have a dedicated fearer for the light blues.
<br />

<br />
Ingenuity - Bard plus mage is the win for this one.  DPS is fully effective against boss, so keep it high.  We kept up a solid 600 DS on tank that tore him up.  Other classes need to kill the gimps for the bane weps, but I stuck with my Horn and Songblade for max DS.
<br />

<br />
Efficiency - Cleric with max Radiant Cure is good.  Everyone needs to stay on center platform and make sure you get the AE off a$ soon as it hits; it goes off every 4 minutes I think.  Otherwise, mez the soldiers, tank the elites and commanders, and just try to preserve mana through the nasty AE.
<br />

<br />
Weaponry - No idea, only one I haven't beaten.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=954899">Kanarian</a>, Bard of Saryrn<br>
Composer of The War Council</span></td>
