			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: MPG Trials<a name="70386"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 28 04 4:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Fear - Bard fear does not work on any of the light blue fearable mobs. Bard's job is to mez the dark blues, and slow mobs. Have a dedicated fearer for the light blues. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is simply not true. Screech lands. Song of Midnight won't because the mobs are immune to changes in run speed and it has a selos component.  I was the only one casting fear in my group and it worked great. And I ususallly didn't have aggro on the feared mobs after it wore off. They ran straight for the MT or cleric even when I was running behind them trying to stay in AE fear range, which is quite small. It is true that the light blue mobs hit harder than the others, but I didn't have trouble when I did get aggro with a shaman watching over my health.The biggeset problem with this trial is the variablilty in the types of mobs. Some rounds won't have any fearlable and others are packed with them.
<br />

<br />
In Efficency we found the soldiers don't hit hard enough to bother mezzing them. My group was basically EP geared, but we lost too much DPS trying to mezz - seemed better for me to keep the DS up. MT on the commander, off-tank on the elites and I AE slowed to keep the soldier off the casters. They hit in the 50s mostly, up to 200.
<br />

<br />
In Ingenuity it is possible to start the trial without aggro'ing the boss. Move around the side hailing till you get a response and stay as far as away as you can and still be able to trigger it. Then back up and fade. If the group can hang tight along the walls you can farm some bane weps fairly quickly before engaging the boss. We had a 12k warrior tank and lost after defensive wore off and the shaman missed a spot heal (he was alternating with cleric CH). Maybe there's a better healing rotation. But if you can get a few banes first, that's less time you need to keep the MT standing. Pets with bane weapons don't lose them, btw. So you may want to equip them first.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
